-- Air France, Banco Santander, Nestle: Europe Equity Preview
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-01-13T05:00:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/air-france-banco-santander-nestle-europe-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  fell 0.2 percent to 249.50. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  retreated 0.6 percent to 2,398.84. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
increased 0.3 percent to 2,345.85.  Air France-KLM Group (AF)  :  Europe ’s biggest airline will
shrink its fleet and freeze pay and hiring at the main French
unit in a push to restore profitability by shaving 1 billion
euros ($1.28 billion) from costs. Air  France  gained 7.5 percent
to 4.29 euros.  Areva SA (AREVA)  (AREVA FP): The former chief executive officer of
the world’s biggest maker of nuclear reactors,  Anne Lauvergeon ,
has filed a lawsuit against the company for non-payment of the
financial package agreed upon when she left seven months ago.
The shares gained 1.8 percent to 18.92 euros.  Banco Espanol de Credito SA  (BTO SM): The Spanish consumer
banking unit of  Banco Santander SA (SAN)   posted a fourth-
quarter loss after it took a 280 million-euro ($356 million)
charge for souring real-estate loans. Banco Espanol climbed 2.8
percent to 3.64 euros.  Banco Santander  SA (SAN SM): The Spanish bank plans to
issue 193.7 million new shares as a dividend payment from last
year’s earnings, the company said in a regulatory filing. Banco
Santander fell 0.7 percent to 5.68 euros.  Bouygues SA (EN)  : France’s second-largest construction
company was named the preferred bidder for a French railroad-
construction contract valued at about 1.3 billion euros ($1.7
billion). Bouygues climbed 0.3 percent to 23.37 euros.  Danone SA (BN)   and  Nestle SA (NESN)  : The food
companies made first-round bids for Pfizer Inc.’s baby-formula
unit, people with knowledge of the matter said. Danone retreated
1.7 percent to 47.56 euros. Nestle fell 0.7 percent to 53.45
francs.  Douglas Holding AG (DOU)  (DOU GY): Henning Kreke, chief executive
of the  European (SXXP)  retailer, plans to team up with a financial
investor to take over the company, Financial Times Deutschland
said, citing unidentified people familiar with the matter.
Douglas rose 26 percent to 32.01 euros.  Solar Millennium AG (S2M)  (S2M GY): The solar company may be
bought as a whole, as there are strategic and financial
investors interested in acquiring the company, Financial Times
Deutschland said, citing comments by Volker Boehm, the company’s
insolvency administrator. Solar Millennium fell 1.9 percent to
27 cents.  To contact the reporters on this story:
